<item>
            <title>[SEC-850] custom-authentication-provider Registering Separate Bean Definitions in App Context and Providers List</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-850</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m seeing multiple instances of the LdapAuthenticationProvider bean when using the traditional bean config. In the namespace config I only see one instance. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So in the samples-ldap app I&apos;m seeing two instances when using the traditional bean config w/ the namespace config commented out and the scope=&quot;singleton&quot; attribute applied to the secondLdapProvider bean definition. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In my app I&apos;m seeing three instances of the LdapAuthenticationProvider bean. It&apos;s like the prototype scope is getting applied.  There&apos;s one instance that&apos;s getting used for authentication, a second instance for a dependency injection bean, not sure about the third instance. I only want ONE shared instance of the LdapAuthenticationProvider bean.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows XP.  JDK 1.6.  Spring Framework 2.5.2</environment>
